funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to conduct a feasibility study for the development of a light industrial parkat the St. Johns Industrial Airport. The proposed Tech Park Ranchis planned to be an advanced agriculture-themed business and technology center that would also include a workforce training facility. The goal of this project is to address the need for sufficient broadband, energy, workforce development, education, and industry due to the loss of jobs that will occur with the planned closing of several nearby coal plants that are currently providing high-paying jobs for the community.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by a nonprofit community organization to provide small business and financial literacy and long-term business strategic planning training for Navajo Nation communities and their leadership. Dine Community Development Corporation will also use project funds to develop a Navajo hemp production feasibility study and business plan to determine the viability of the hemp business concept, such as ensuring the legal and technical feasibility and economic justification. The study will encompass the proposal of an industrial hemp production facility on the Navajo Nation as well as the creation of a Commission to oversee all hemp operations within the reservation. A business plan will then be developed from the results of the feasibility study for a viable hemp business opportunity. These projects will address the Navajo Nations high unemployment rate while increasing local economic development activities. The project is expected to save seven and create fourteen jobs.

funding_code: RURAL BUSINESS-COOPERATIVE SERVICE - RURAL INNOVATION STRONGER ECONOMY GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment will be used to establish the St. Johns Innovation Center to assist new and existing businesses and job seekers; develop a business recruitment/retention plan to increase economic development activities in the region; create a Talent Pipeline Management program to focus on workforce development between public-private organizations; and create expanded training systems linked to industry cluster employer needs leading to higher-paying jobs in the rural energy distressed communities of Navajo and Apache Counties in Arizona.

funding_code: SMALL SOCIALLY DISADVANTAGED PRODUCER GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a Navajo Financial Cooperative program for the Navajo Nation and surrounding tribal communities. The proposed Navajo Financial Cooperative Feasibility Study and Business Plan will be used to develop a reservation-based financial/credit union cooperative program where a Din/Native American-owned financial institution can help combat credit deserts in rural and Indigenous areas. The Navajo Nation lacks access to financial entities, and the surrounding rural communities as well; and financial cooperatives and credit unions help strengthen the economy and empower people with ownership over their financial institution. The objective of establishing a Navajo Financial Cooperative is to develop a reservation-based credit union such as a type of financial institution similar to a commercial bank that will be a Navajo member-owned financial cooperative, controlled by its Navajo/Native American members and operated on a not-for-profit basis. The financial/credit union coop will provide services to members similar to retail banks, including deposit accounts, provision of credit, and other financial services that is currently lacking on the reservation.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help a non profit organization with site preparation, utility connections, site design, consultation for modular base set-up, concrete pads for modular buildings, and installation of buildings. Funding will enable the Foundation for Little Colorado Revitalization to provide services like transportation, distribution, and marketing of food to local retail and wholesale outlets. These vital infrastructure services will benefit 13,456 rural residents located in Springerville, Northern Apache County, Navajo County, Arizona and Western New Mexico.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help The Foundation for Little Colorado Revitalization, a local non-profit dedicated to enhancing rural quality of life, purchase food processing equipment, a mobile harvest/delivery truck, an aging cooler, cut and wrap module, and pay certification fees. This equipment will enable them to provide services to include the transportation, distribution, and marketing of food to local retail and wholesale outlets for 13,456 residents in Springerville, Northern Apache County and Navajo County, Arizona, and Western New Mexico.

funding_code: ECONOMIC IMPACT INITIATIVE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by a non profit organization for site preparation, utility connections, site design, consultation for modular base set-up, concrete pads for modular buildings, and installation of buildings. Funding will enable the Foundation for Little Colorado Revitalization to provide services like transportation, distribution, and marketing of food to local retail and wholesale outlets. These vital infrastructure services will benefit 13,456 rural residents located in Springerville, Northern Apache County, Navajo County, Arizona and Western New Mexico.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two generators for Apache County. Apache Countrys current administrative and satellite offices do not have generators for backup power. The addition of new generators will allow the county to continue to provide services including the operation of road crews, during emergencies and inclement weather.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install solar lighting equipment around the perimeter of two administration buildings for Apache County. Currently their administrative offices do not have sufficient lighting at night and the energy efficient equipment purchased will allow staff to work in a safer environment.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a wood processor, logging trailer, commercial chain saws and other wood cutting equipment for Apache County, located in the northeast corner of Arizona. Apache County assists the Navajo Nation and the Fort Apache Indian Reservation elders by providing cut firewood to heat their homes. Purchasing their own wood cutting equipment allows them to stockpile more cut firewood earlier in the year, assisting about 290 elderly families each winter. This project not only provides heating for the elderly, but this project also removes dead and downed trees from forested areas, preventing the spread of potential wildfires.

funding_code: NATIVE AMERICAN TRIBES COMMUNITY FACILITY GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for the Dine College Tsaile Demonstration Farm Development to complete the livestock holding facility and space, steel indoor structure, support utilities to the building, and ground and foundation work; which will be used for the education of handing livestock.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fund the preparation of a Preliminary Engineering Report and Environmental Report for a homeowners association in Cochise County, Arizona. Coronado Lakes Estates Homeowners Association will use these reports to evaluate and produce a solution for the existing oversized and leaking waterline connected to nine homes in the distressed community of Douglas, Arizona.

funding_code: B&I CORONAVIRUS AID, RELIEF AND ECONOMIC SECURITY ACT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital to support the Quality Inn in Page, Ariz. in meeting its operating expenses during the economic downturn the tourism economy has experienced due to the pandemic. This assistance will aid in the retention of 45 jobs at the hotel and the restaurant operating within the hotel.

funding_code: B&I CORONAVIRUS AID, RELIEF AND ECONOMIC SECURITY ACT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to support and sustain successful operations of an existing motel and restaurant in Williams, AZ, also located in a Opportunity Zone.Thisloan will assist the borrower in meeting their working capital needs during the COVID-19 pandemic, which includes important safety and cleaning protocols, while ensuring affordable rates to their cliental. An estimated 24 jobs will be saved in a community heavily reliant on Grand Canyon tourism.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the borrower in purchasing an existing 120-room mid-scale, limited service hotel in Williams, Coconino County, Ariz. This property is a critical piece of infrastructure to meet the lodging needs of travelers to the Grand Canyon National Park and other tourist attractions in the region. The Borrower is contributing $1,948,000 and the project is expected to save 30 jobs.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Williams Lodging 710 LLC in purchasing and making improvements to a 48-room mid-scale, limited service hotel in Williams, Coconino County, Arizona. This property is a critical piece of infrastructure to meet the lodging needs of travelers to the Grand Canyon National Park and other tourist attractions in the region. The project is expected to save 15 jobs.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a Railway Access Plan feasibility study to determine and recommend the best use of the existing rail infrastructure at Camp Navajo and how it can benefit small businesses in rural Coconino County.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist in the funding a feasibility study to determine whether the Leupp Chapter, Bird Springs Chapter, and Tolani Lake Chapter should further develop approximately 2,500 acres of land set aside for farming. The environmental portion of the study would identify soils types, usable acreage, water requirements and availability, location and access to infrastructure. The business portion of the study would also determine the appropriate structure of business(es), business planning and projections for long term sustainability, and benefits to the community. This project is located in an Opportunity Zone as well as a distressed community. The Leupp Chapter is contributing $50,000 toward the project.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to prepare an Economic Development and Resiliency Recovery Plan (EDRRP) for the City of Page. Page has been impacted by the closure of the Navajo Generating Station and by reduced tourism spending due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This project is expected to save 50 jobs.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help with technical assistance and training ($68,203) and to establish a revolving loan fund of $50,000 to assist micro-businesses on the Navajo Nation and Hopi Indian Reservation. This project is expected to create two jobs and save nine in a community with a poverty rate of 25.4 percent.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fund critical safety and infrastructure upgrades to the Sedona Art Barn, including electrical improvements and fire suppression systems. The Art Barn host classes, workshops and provides gallery space to artists in the Sedona area. Artists are small businesses that live and work in the community.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND. RENEW ENERFY SYSTEMS GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Forestdale Farm LLC, a small family-run organic produce farm in rural Flagstaff, Arizona, purchase a 1.7-kilowatt (kW) photovoltaic system with battery backup. The improvements are expected to generate 2,555 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year, equivalent to 25 percent of the usage of a typical U.S. home. More importantly the battery backup will allow the farms water well pump motor to run without a generator and is expected to reduce the farms expenses $3,000 per year, savings the farm can invest back into its operations.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investmentwill be used to continue the STAR School Water Technical Assistance and Training Program in the Navajo Nation and Hopi Tribes. funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to drill a deep-water well for the town of Pine-Strawberry in northern Arizona. Arizona is now facing a water crisis that could dry up rural areas all over the state. This well will enable the Pine-Strawberry Water Improvement District to increase the water supply for 3,034 residents in this rural community. A deep-water well has a better chance of continuing to produce water during a drought because it is closer to the aquifer than the shallow wells currently in place.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)

This well will enable the Pine-Strawberry Water Improvement District to increase the water supply for 3,034 residents in this rural community. funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
naics_description: ALL OTHER MISCELLANEOUS SCHOOLS AND INSTRUCTION
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by a community organization to continue to rehabilitate the historic Safford Theater in southeast Arizona. The Safford Downtown Association will use this grant to complete the stage area installation and purchase the audio and visual equipment for the theater rehabilitation project. The association is comprised of local business owners who work to improve downtown Safford through events, capital improvement projects, business support and reinvestment. The renovated space will offer an outdoor theater for live performances, a movie screen, a courtyard, and an indoor performance stage. The purpose of restoring the theatre is to create an economic engine on the street that brings more people downtown to support their rural businesses.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY CF GRANTS

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the Safford Downtown Association continue its rehabilitation of the historic Safford Theater in southeast Arizona. The grant will be used to complete the stage area installation and purchase the audio and visual equipment for the theater rehabilitation project. The association is comprised of local business owners who work to improve downtown Safford through events, capital improvement projects, business support and reinvestment. The renovated space will offer an outdoor theater for live performances, a movie screen, a courtyard, and an indoor performance stage. The theatre restoration project aims to support the growth of rural business by drawing new clientele to the downtown area.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to equip the northwest Arizona border town of Parkers Law Enforcement Department with an essential communication system. The department will use the grant to purchase a unified communication system that allows the town to share information and coordinate with the public safety and first responders in Parker and the surrounding towns.Because of the warm winter climate and location on the Colorado River, Parker sees an increase in tourism through the winter months. The new equipment enables the department to continue meet the health and safety needs of 3,083 rural residents and the estimated 10,000 annual visitors.

borrower_name: INTER TRIBAL COUNCIL OF ARIZONA INC
funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist member tribes in effectively managing and mitigating solid waste to protect the environment on tribal lands and the health of American Indians. Inter Tribal Council of Arizona will conduct trainings for tribal members and tribal solid waste personnel on specific landfill issues, stormwater management, large vehicle management, birds and other vectors, and litter mitigation, diversion rates in the United States, Occupational Safety and Health Administration safety pertaining to landfill and transfer station workers, Hazardous Waste Operations and Emergency Response refresher course, and composting.

borrower_name: INTER TRIBAL COUNCIL OF ARIZONA INC
funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used toprovide its technical assistance, training, and tribal operator certification services to small, rural tribal communities located in USEPA Regions 5 through 10-a project service area spanning 28 states and 96 percent of all tribal public water systems in the U.S. The following four project activities will be implemented. First, ITCA will strengthen tribal water utility resilience by providing resiliency technical assistance (TA) and conducting resiliency training. Second, ITCA will strengthen tribal utility managerial and financial (M&F) capacity by providing M&F-TA, conducting Tribal Utility Tune-Up (EUM "workshop in a box")Workshops, and conducting training-Tribal Utility Management Certification training, as well as training on utility finance, asset management, and water loss control. Third, ITCA will strengthen tribal utility operations & maintenance (O&M) capacity by providing O&M-TA, conducting operator fundamentals trainings and free regional tribal operator certification training events, offering travel reimbursement stipends, and creating a new type of tribal operator certification for tribal wastewater lagoon operators. In addition, ITCA will improve the workforce pipeline by exploring potentials for developing workforce pipeline linkages with tribal colleges and universities. Fourth, ITCA will improve tribal water utility capacity for complying with federal regulations by conducting federal regulations training events.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to design the hub-and-spoke recycling programs in Arizona by providing technical assistance and training to allow rural regions to offer recycling services to rural communities and develop effective outreach programs to maximize participation from residents. The communities to be engaged in this project are: Bisbee, Tombstone, Pirtleville, Huachuca City, St. David, Pinetop-Lakeside, Heber-Overgaard, White Mountain Lake, Springerville, and Whiteriver, Arizona.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to partially fund an Anaerobic Digester facility located on the Butterfield Dairy near Gila Bend, Arizona. The digester will convert cow manure into renewable natural gas (RNG) to be inserted into a nearby pipeline and ultimately used for transportation fuel in California, earning Low Carbon Fuel Standards (LCFS) credits in addition to the revenue from the sale of the RNG. The facility will generate 90,111,079 kWh of energy per year, or the equivalent of 8,462 US homes. The project is also expected to generate revenues in excess of $24 million annually, a portion of which will remain in the local community.

funding_code: B&I CORONAVIRUS AID, RELIEF AND ECONOMIC SECURITY ACT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to support and sustain successful operations of an existing inland shrimp farm located near Gila Bend, AZ. This project is also located in a Opportunity Zone and a Distressed Community. This B&I CARES Act guaranteed loan will assist the borrower in meeting their immediate working capital needs and assist them in recovering from the devastating impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic. An estimated six jobs will be saved.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Dilkon Chapter of the Navajo Nation with their Economic Development Project. The project consists of conducting a small business workshop, an economic and community development leadership workshop, chapter strategic planning session, and a community-based economic development feasibility study. The study will assist the chapter in meeting their short and long-term strategic goals of creating economic development opportunities to provide local jobs, entertainment options, and cultural activities in Dilkon. The project is expected to create 28 and save 43 jobs.

funding_code: SECTION 306 FFB - OTHER ELECTRIC FFB - OTHER LOAN PERSISTENT POVERTY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to connect 1,340 consumers and build and improve 636 miles of line. This loan will also fund transmission expansions and upgrades, headquarters and warehouse construction and the acquisition of 5,337 consumers, 144 miles of transmission line, and 221 miles of distribution line near Tuba City (owned by Arizona Public Service) and on the Hopi Reservation. This loan includes $29,412,189 in smart grid technologies including 304 miles of backbone fiber and 27 miles will be customer drops. NTUA is headquartered in Fort Defiance, Arizona, serving approximately 41,500 accounts, over 10,698 miles of line in 6 counties in Arizona, Utah, and New Mexico.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to acquire high-quality video conferencing equipment for 22 rural schools throughout eastern Arizona. The program will enable expanded access to college coursework as project sites commit to supplying and offering access to dual enrollment coursework to high school students during the day. Funded equipment will also be used for college and career prep for adult learners, taught during evenings, and courses leading to degrees in Early Childhood Education (ECD) and Education (EDU) taught on weekends. The project will serve over 1,100 rural residents at across a 21,158 square-mile area, that includes the tribal lands of the Navajo, Hopi and White Mountain Apache people.

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND 100% GRANT- RBS REDG SUB ACCOUNT SEC. 762- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network in rural Arizona. The funded service area includes 5,547 households, 22,645 people, an educational facility, nine essential community facilities, a health care facility, six farms and 142 businesses spread over 59 square miles.

funding_code: BUSINESS & INDUSTRY GUARANTEED LOAN - 1%
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for the construction and permanent financing of a restaurant, gift shop, and hotel in Summerhaven, AZ. The project will create 10 jobs in a rural community adversely impact by the Bighorn Fire that occurred in June/July 2020. The Borrower is contributing $2,092,867 toward the total development costs.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to stimulate the economically depressed economy of the Pascua Yaqui Tribe by evaluating and assessing the feasibility of marketing needs and providing marketing plans for four tribal business enterprises. The end result of the project is expected to save one and create 58 jobs.

funding_code: DISCRETION ASSIST MICROPENTERPRENUERS
naics_industry_sector: Finance and Insurance (52)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used continue to provide technical assistance and training in southeastern Arizona in conjunction with the recipients revolving loan fund established for their Arizona Border Business Crisis Empowerment Program. Loan and business counseling services will be provided to small businesses in underserved rural communities by working with prospective applicants and existing borrowers to build financial capacity, develop short and long term strategies, and access capital resources.

funding_code: DISCRETION ASSIST MICROPENTERPRENUERS
naics_industry_sector: Finance and Insurance (52)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to continue to provide initial and ongoing technical assistance to new and existing microentrepreneurs and microenterprises in southern rural Arizona who are eligible to access to the Rural Microentrepreneur Assistance Program loan funds.

funding_code: LAMP BEGINNING AND SOCIALLY DISADVANTAGED FARMERS OR RANCHERS GRANTS - COVID
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: OTHER VEGETABLE (EXCEPT POTATO) AND MELON FARMING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help defray the costs of a feasibility study and marketing plan for Merchants Garden AgroTech Inc., a minority-owned family farm.These activities will allow the business to pre-package and market locally-grown, fresh and nutritious salad mixes, largely from produce that would otherwise be unsaleable and discarded solely due to minor visual imperfections. The ability to sell additional products from previously wasted produce should significantly boost the business bottom line.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase furniture and equipment for the Art Studio, Science Laboratory, and classrooms in the new Arts and Sciences Building on the Tohono Oodham Community College Main Campus in Sells, Arizona.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fund the preparation of the Preliminary Engineering Report and Environmental Report to identify and address the Why, Arizona. water system issues.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: FREESTANDING AMBULATORY SURGICAL AND EMERGENCY CENTERS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase furniture, fixtures, machinery, and equipment for the critically needed hospital in the rural community of Maricopa, Pinal County, Arizona. Exceptional Health Care Maricopa will be the first specialty internal medicine hospital and 24-hour emergency department in this rural community that serves 43,482 residents. The state-of-the-art facility includes digital imaging, an in-house laboratory, and outpatient and inpatient hospital beds for acute admissions and overnight observation of patients.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to partially fund an Anaerobic Digester facility located on the Milky Way Dairy near Maricopa, Arizona. The digester will convert cow manure into renewable natural gas (RNG) to be inserted into a nearby pipeline and ultimately used for transportation fuel in California, earning Low Carbon Fuel Standards (LCFS) credits in addition to the revenue from the sale of the RNG. The facility will generate 118,405,627 kWh of energy per year, or the equivalent of 11,119 US homes. The project is also expected to generate revenues in excess of $32 million annually, a portion of which will remain in the local community.

funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to re-develop the Copper Communities Supplier Portal website. The Copper Corridor Economic Development Coalition business directory will be updated with proper American Disabilities Act accessibility and will add a procurement module for uploading requests for proposals and requests for qualifications from larger companies and local governments allowing smaller local businesses to bid on those opportunities. Another component will be added that allows local businesses to expand their outreach by providing them the opportunity to develop their own micro sales websites.

naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to refinance debt into a single more affordable loan.Flying Leap Vineyards will use the funds to purchase equipment and construct a finished goods warehouse and a supply warehouse/shipping facility. The additional facilities will enable the borrower to properly store and ship their wine and spirits to meet increasing demand for their products.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY RBCS BUSINESS ENTERPRISE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to contract with an organization to build a unified digital platform/dashboard in the ruralU.S.-Mexico border area in Santa Cruz County, Arizona. The digital platform will allow small businesses in rural communities outside of the city of Nogales to digitally market themselves (in lieu of the County Chamber of Commerce) and enable tourists and local residents to access services and shop local. This funding is expected to create nine jobs and save eight in the Nogales area, a designated distressed community in persistent poverty, located in Santa Cruz County.

funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Transportation and Warehousing (48-49)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help a rural greenhouse operator in Amado, Arizona, install a 205.8kW solar photovoltaic system. The Wholesum Family Farms all-glass greenhouse, located in the designated persistent poverty county of Santa Cruz, delivers a consistent supply of healthy and delicious organic produce year-round. The system is expected to generate 367,805kWh of electricity annually, or enough to power 34 average U.S. homes, saving the company over $40,000 each year in utility bills, savings they can invest back into operations.

naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to refinance a seller note to enable the borrower to improve its cash flow at this 51-unit RV Park in Black Canyon City, Yavapai County, Arizona. Two jobs will be saved.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase the Days Inn and Suites in Camp Verde, Ariz. The project will allow hotel operations to continue to provide lodging services to business and leisure travelers visiting the local area and will assist in retaining 16 jobs and adding three additional positions in this opportunity zone located in Yavapai County, Ariz.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Retail Trade (44-45)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Cypress Gates Inc. purchase a commercial building currently leased by a major retail sporting goods outlet in Cottonwood, Arizona. Commercial real estate is critical infrastructure for rural Arizona communities, especially when occupied by a strong brand retail store. A major sporting goods outlet in Yavapai county also contributes to the tourism economy with visitors using the recreational opportunities this rural area offers and saves 20 jobs.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment will be used to establish training sessions and workshops, and to provide one-on-one mentoring for five small businesses currently housed in the "Center for the Future," a high-tech business incubator in the City of Prescott, Arizona. The goal for the five businesses (and other local high-tech businesses) isto expand their cyber footprint and grow their businesses by increasing employment and providing high quality wages. The project is expected to create 12 jobs.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a workforce development internship program with Northern Arizona University and small businesses located in Camp Verde, Cottonwood, and Sedona, Arizona. This regional partnership initiative seeks to retain the Universitys talent pipeline in the northern Arizona area by bringing awareness to local career options while providing a skilled workforce for local rural businesses. The project is expected to create at least five jobs.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Levi Arcadia, an assisted living facility in Prescott, Arizona, install a 305.3kW solar photovoltaic system. The system is expected to generate 520,500kWh of electricity annually saving the business over $64,000 on their utility bills each year, savings they can invest back into their operations.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MAND ENERGY EFF IMPROV GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
naics_description: LESSORS OF RESIDENTIAL BUILDINGS AND DWELLINGS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Levi Arcadia, a rural Assisted Living facility, retrofit its lighting to more energy efficient LED lights. The new lighting is expected to use 936,713kWh less energy each year, enough to power 86 average United States homes. The reduction in usage will save the business $115,186 in utility bills each year, savings they can invest back into their operations.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Arts, Entertainment, and Recreation (71)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to refinance debt, make repairs and improvements to the facilitys foundation, HVAC system, electrical, fire sprinkler alarms, security alarms, cameras, window tinting, and flooring, and also to purchase furniture and equipment.

borrower_name: BLACK CANYON COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER INC
funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
naics_description: LESSORS OF OTHER REAL ESTATE PROPERTY
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to upgrade optical-fiber, internet, and information technology equipment, purchase an automated defibrillator, and renovate the Black Canyon Community Health Center in southern Yavapai Country, Arizona. This rural health center is a medical group practice that specializes in family medicine providing primary, dental, mental health, cardiology care, and pharmacy services including outreach, enrollment, case management and transportation. This investment will improve and reinforce the centers capacity to serve the 2,825 residents of this rural community.

funding_code: (SECD) CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESIDENTIAL INTELLECTUAL AND DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITY FACILITIES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve a four-plex housing facility, recently donated by a local non-profit, in Cottonwood.. It will be used by women of all ages who are in the substance abuse recovery program. Improvements will include added security features, floors, roofing, heating and cooling, solar panels, an outdoor storage structure, equipment and furniture. Steps to Recovery Homes offers housing, transportation, job skill coaching, and essential services to help clients manage their day-to-day lives.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESIDENTIAL INTELLECTUAL AND DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITY FACILITIES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve a four-plex housing facility, recently donated by a local non-profit, in Cottonwood.. It will be used by women of all ages who are in the substance abuse recovery program. Improvements will include added security features, floors, roofing, heating and cooling, solar panels, an outdoor storage structure, equipment and furniture. Steps to Recovery Homes offers housing, transportation, job skill coaching, and essential services to help clients manage their day-to-day lives.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESIDENTIAL INTELLECTUAL AND DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITY FACILITIES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make improvements to a four-plex housing facility located in Cottonwood, Arizona. The facility was donated to Steps to Recovery Homes by a local non-profit and will be used by women of all ages who are in their substance abuse recovery program. To allow occupancy and to lower operation costs, the facility needs improvements. The improvements to be made are to add security features, install flooring, roofing, heating and cooling, solar panels, an outdoor storage structure, and purchase equipment and furniture. Steps to Recovery Homes offers housing, utilities, linens, laundry and cleaning supplies, transportation, job skill coaching, and essentials to manage their clients day to day lives.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used make water system improvements in Tacna, Arizona. The Yuma County Improvement District will develop and construct a new water treatment and distribution system, remove and replace more than 1,000 linear feet of aging or low capacity pipe to include service connections, and the construction of a new water storage tank and groundwater well, at a new location away from the residential area. The current system is more than 40 years old and has been deemed unfeasible to rehabilitate and the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality placed an Administrative Order on the water system deeming the water non-drinkable due to high Arsenic levels dating back to 2011. The water system improvements will provide safe and reliable drinking water for 672 residents.

The project is expected to save seven jobs and create 22.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to inspect, rehabilitate, and or replace the water system infrastructure, and replace the reverse osmosis system for San Simon Water Improvement District. The current water source contains elevated amounts of fluoride and is out of compliance with Environmental Protection Agency and Arizona Department of Environmental Quality standards. The facility consists of a well, three storage tanks, two booster stations, one hydropneumatics tank, a chlorine system, and an inoperable reverse osmosis system that requires rehabilitation or replacement due to age. The San Simon Water Improvement District provides water service to the San Simon Community in Cochise County, Arizona.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to drill a well, install water lines, storage tank, and booster pump to cure the health and sanitary issues of the current water distribution system for a community north of Douglas, Arizona. The system was installed in the 1970s, is in excess of its design life, and and has multiple leaks and breaks. This results in contaminants being introduced into the potable water system, causing a health and sanitary, and maintenance and financial hardship issues.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to grant funds to expand Northern Arizona Technology and Business Incubators AZ Stitch Lab program to the Navajo Nation and the Hardrock Chapter in Navajo County, Arizona. The grantee will provide up to 12 weeks of training in industrial sewing, entrepreneurship, and the use of innovative materials. After training, the participants will be able to work at a company that needs industrial sewing skills or be able to start their own business.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist North Leupp Family Farms, Inc. to develop a master plan for the space layout of a food hub. It will expand marketing activities by developing Sunrise Mobile Market, upgrading solar infrastructure, improving the existing post-harvest infrastructure, and providing technical assistance to small and emerging businesses in the Navajo Nation. North Leupp Family Farms is a community-based farm co-op that supports Navajo families and local agriculture.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create a master plan for a small business development near the new Echo Cliffs Health Clinic near the Coppermine Chapter on the Navajo Nation in Coconino County, Arizona. The master plan will study potential sites, engage the community in incorporating their needs, develop preliminary and draft concept plans, and provide a final master plan and report.

funding_code: SMALL SOCIALLY DISADVANTAGED PRODUCER GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide be used to provide technical assistance and training to socially disadvantaged groups to promote cooperative development, primarily on the Navajo Nation and Hopi Reservation as well as other Native American tribes in Arizona and the surrounding states. North Leupp Family Farms is a community-based farm coop which supports Navajo families and local agriculture.

funding_code: COMBINATION CF DIRECT LOAN/GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to renovate three buildings and purchase equipment for Page Regional Domestic Violence Services. The organization assists people in poverty, single parents, domestic violence victims, and parents seeking reunification with their children. Due to lacking services and high community need, the organizations large service area includes Navajo Nation, Page, Flagstaff, Southern Utah, and other Tribes throughout the country. Renovations will include creating a commercial health food store, a residential laundry facility, a commercial kitchen, communal eatery, and an outdoor patio to provide an area for meetings and services. This project will enable Page Regional Domestic Violence Services to provide instruction and certification for food handling and cultivating fresh produce via dry farming, and provide retail work and food service experience.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and replace a solar pump controller for the well used by a small farm cooperative. North Leupp Family Farms is a community-based farm coop which supports Navajo families and local agriculture. A well is the source of the irrigation water for the farm cooperative and the current controller for the solar system is no longer working. Installing a solar system will reduce the farm cooperatives utilities expenses, freeing up funds to be used for other farm needs.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C-NATIVE AMERICAN-WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system improvements for Painted Desert Demonstration Projects Inc., which is a nonprofit organization serving Tribal residents in northern Arizona. This project will replace a 84,500 gallon water storage tank with a 150,000 gallon tank and expand the on-site solar system to power water pumping for the water system. Seventy-two percent of the homes in the immediate vicinity do not have running water, and the need for clean drinking water was accentuated by the COVID-19 pandemic. This project will provide treated, monitored water so that residents of the Navajo Nation and Hopi Tribes, who are currently hauling water, have access to point-of-service watering stations that provide safe, clean drinking water.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to continue the STAR School Water Technical Assistance and Training Program. This long-standing program works to generate meaningful solutions and results for regional water safety and security. This program will deliver the services of Community Outreach and Needs Assessment, In-community Technology Demonstration and Training, Direct Technical Assistance, and Commitment to Lasting Results and Long-Term Sustainability through community education, interviews, site visits, surveys, workshops, demonstration projects, hands-on training, distribution of educational materials, technical assistance, and developing local capacity/workforce. The former Bennett Freeze Reservation, the broader Navajo Nation, Hopi Tribe, San Carlos Apache Indian Reservation, and other Native American Reservations. The rural communities served by this program have a population of less than 2,500.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make improvements to the city of Saffords water distribution system. This project includes installing waterlines to provide service to unserved residential areas, and connecting residents to the waterlines, located outside the city limits, but within their service area. This investment will also be used to enhance the citys ability to provide source water while maintaining capacity to the homes. The reliability and security of the citys water supply is frequently undermined by breaks in the 80-year old aged water lines. These events may introduce contaminants into the system. In addition, water supply is limited by narrow transmission lines. To accommodate continued growth, these lines must be upsized.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to make improvements to the Bouse Domestic Water Improvement District water system and bring it up to Arizona Department of Environmental Quality standards. The undersized water lines will be replaced, system will be upgraded with drive-by meters, a water treatment system will be installed for arsenic removal, an operations building added, both a new well and a 70,000 gallon water storage tank will be developed, and other necessary additions to bring the aged system up to modern standards.

borrower_name: TOWN OF QUARTZSITE MUNICIPAL PROPERTY CORPORATION
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to expand sewer service to residential and commercial customers, and to eliminate the use of on-site septic tank treatment systems in Quartzsite, Arizona. 25,000 linear feet of sewer line, 61 new manholes, and residential and commercial connections will be installed. The residents in the project area are on septic systems and leach fields that contribute to elevated nitrate levels found in the groundwater. Constructing this wastewater collection system will reduce the amount of nitrogen that is introduced into the groundwater.

funding_code: CF TAT GRANT (SECTION 6006)
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: The Rural Development investment will be used to provide technical assistance and training to the four ultimate recipient target communities of Duncan, Springerville, Hayden, and the San Carlos Apache Indian Reservation in Bylas, Arizona. The project will develop community facility strategic plans focusing on recovering economically from the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic; ensure equitable access to community programming and benefits; and reduce climate pollution and increase resilience to the impacts of climate change through identification and planning for projects that advance economic support to the community.

borrower_name: INTER TRIBAL COUNCIL OF ARIZONA INC
funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Inter Tribal Council of Arizona (ITCA) train member Tribes to effectively manage and mitigate solid waste. Training will be given to Tribal solid waste and environmental professionals on specific landfill issues, how to prevent fires caused by landfills, worker accidents and safety, the business of solid waste, cost of operations of a landfill, transfer stations, and the benefits of outsourcing management, composting projects in smaller Tribal communities, and hazardous waste treatment and cleanup refresher course. ITCA is a non-profit corporation offering technical assistance and training to Tribal governments.

borrower_name: INTER TRIBAL COUNCIL OF ARIZONA INC
funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to implement three project activities: Strengthen technical, managerial, and financial capacity of tribal water utilities by conducting comprehensive operator training and certification services, offering travel expense reimbursement stipends, and providing technical assistance. Strengthen tribal water utility resilience by providing resiliency technical assistance (TA) and conducting resiliency training, including training on asset management and water loss control. Improve tribal water utility capacity for complying with federal regulations by conducting federal regulations training and certification services.

naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)

The project is estimated to create 18 jobs. This project will be the only dedicated truck and RV wash near the I-10 exit 162 and adjacent to the third busiest Loves truck stop in the U.S.

funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Dilkon Chapter of the Navajo Nation with an economic development project. The project consists of developing a community land use plan to assist the Chapter in creating economic and community development opportunities that meet their short and long-term strategic goals. The ultimate goal is to achieve tribal self-sufficiency to improve the overall quality of life of entrepreneurs by creating a diversified, job-generating private sector capable of supporting and increasing job creation efforts in Dilkon, Ariz. The project is expected to create 32 jobs and save six.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a master plan that will support, "Rock the Canyon," an annual music and arts festival in the Shonto Chapter area on the Navajo Nation in Navajo County, Arizona. The master plan process will study expansion of the festival, research and recommend venue options, including sites, stages and venues for artisans, as well as facilitate business visioning sessions for those businesses that will benefit from the annual festival.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install electricity to teacher housing that serves Dischiibikoh Community School. The school district will build two additional housing fourplexes to provide on-site housing for more teachers. The school uses the housing as a recruitment tool since the nearest housing is located 150 miles away, and there is not enough teacher housing available in the area. This school serves families of Cibecue and surrounding areas of the White Mountain Apache Tribe reservation.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install sewer connections to teacher housing at Dischiibikoh Community School. The school district will build two additional housing fourplexes to provide on-site housing for more of its teachers. The school uses the housing as a recruitment tool since the nearest housing is located 150 miles away, and there is not enough teacher housing available in the area.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase four mobile light towers that will provide lighting for the football field at Dishchiibikoh Community School. The school offers classes for students in kindergarten through grade 12 and was founded to serve the children and families of Cibecue and the surrounding communities on the White Mountain Apache Reservation. The football field is currently unlit and the school is unable to hold practice and games after dark. The new lighting will enable the school to safely hold night games during the fall when daylight hours get shorter

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network to connect 4,784 people, 27 businesses, 10 educational facilities and two farms to high-speed internet in Navajo County in Arizona. Navajo Tribal Utility Company will make high-speed internet affordable by participating in the FCCs Affordable Connectivity Program. This project will serve the Navajo Nation Reservation and socially vulnerable communities in Navajo County.

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND 100% GRANT- RBS REDG SUB ACCOUNT SEC. 762- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network. This network will connect 201 people, seven businesses and two farms to high-speed internet in Apache County. Table Top Telephone Company Inc. will make high-speed internet affordable by offering 100 megabits per second symmetrical service free for residents that participate in the Federal Communications Commissions Lifeline Affordable Connectivity Programs. This project will serve socially vulnerable communities in Apache County and will serve the Navajo Nation Reservation.

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network to connect 1,624 people, 123 farms, 11 businesses and four educational facilities in Maricopa, Pima, and Pinal counties in Arizona. Tohono Oodham Utility Authority will make high-speed internet affordable by participating in the FCCs Lifeline and Affordable Connectivity programs. This project will serve socially vulnerable communities in Maricopa, Pima and Pinal counties as well as the Tohono Oodham Nation Reservation and Tohono Oodham Nation Off-Reservation Trust Land.

program: Telecommunications Infrastructure Loans and Loan Guarantees (TELE)
funding_code: TELE SECTION 305 VARIABLE TELE TREASURY RATE - LOAN PERSISTENT POVERTY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to upgrade the systems 13 exchanges in southeast Arizona and southwest New Mexico by replacing copper wire-based equipment with fiber-to-the-premises equipment. A total of 1,317 miles of buried fiber-optic cable will be laid and 2,755 optical network terminals will be installed along with optical line terminals, fiber panels, fiber distribution mainframes, and other upgraded equipment. This will result in improved broadband service that is capable of providing both upload and download data rates of up to one gigabit per second for every subscriber simultaneously, in addition to enhanced voice services.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to renovate a 10,000 square-foot space in the main plaza of Ajo, Arizona to expand the Ajo Business Support Center to meet their demand for business services and training. The new center will promote economic development and job creation. Additions will include a fabrication space, a co-working/land manager outreach space, and an area to offer business training and workshops. This project is expected to assist 65 local businesses, entrepreneurs, and/or startups, while saving twenty jobs and creating four new employment opportunities.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to perform the necessary business planning activities required to create a business plan for the Career Pivot Center that will be located on the Pascua Pueblo Yaqui Reservation. The Center will initially provide construction trades certification and related workforce development training services for three tribally owned businesses and will tailor subsequent training offerings to meet the needs of other new and emerging tribally owned companies. The Career Pivot Center will provide an opportunity for tribal members to receive training and obtain the skills necessary to qualify for well-paying employment options. The project is expected to save eight jobs during the project period and an additional 10 jobs through 2025.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the community with recovery after its food bank ceased operations in early into the COVID-19 pandemic. Ajo Center for Sustainable Agriculture promotes and supports a sustainable local food system in Ajo, Arizona and the Tohono Oodham Nation. This project will support a new food bank facility and food distribution needs, providing the emergency food response, and the development of a new emergency food system, which includes facility improvements, equipment, and operating expenses associated with the newly established Ajo Food Pantry.

funding_code: NATIVE AMERICAN TRIBES COMMUNITY FACILITY GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
naics_description: ALL OTHER MISCELLANEOUS SCHOOLS AND INSTRUCTION
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to increase the solar generated electric power on the Tohono Oodham Community College main campus located in Sells, Arizona. This will expand a previous project and provide shaded parking for an additional one quarter of the remaining parking areas. The utility cost savings will provide funding toward the goal of all parking to be shaded with the covered parking and solar panels, provide substantial electrical generation, and further cost savings.

naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make interior improvements and to establish and relocate the Town of Superior council chambers, administration offices, senior center, community kitchen, business accelerator classrooms, and community event room. The first building was constructed in 1926 and the changes and construction over the many years since then must be brought up to modern standards.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to rehabilitate and make improvements to the town of Kearnys water system, distribution lines, and meters. The town of Kearny operates a public water system located within Pinal County, Arizona. The system includes four wells, two steel water storage tanks, one booster station with hydro pneumatic tank, a water treatment plant (filtration plant), and 10.3 miles of distribution pipeline. The water meters are more than 20 years old and water loss is shown at 27 percent. Improvements will enable the town to supply potable water to customers, will increase system efficiency and avoid seeking additional water sources, conserve water, and provide reliable service.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to rehabilitate the waste water treatment plant and make improvements to the collection system, including the lift stations, gravity sewer piping, and 60 manholes. The improvements are necessary in order for this aging system, designed in 1974, to maintain regulatory compliance, and will ensure reliability and long term compliance with environmental permits. This is a long-term investment in the health and growth of the town of Superior, Arizona.

naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
naics_description: LESSORS OF MINIWAREHOUSES AND SELF-STORAGE UNITS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment investment will be used to help Crossroads Self Storage LLC purchase and install a 20.6-kilowatt roof-mounted solar PV. The system will generate 33,648 kilowatt hours of renewable electricity per year, which is enough to power 5.1 gasoline powered passenger vehicles driven for one year. funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: OFFICES OF PHYSICIANS, MENTAL HEALTH SPECIALISTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to expand regional mental health care through new telehealth capabilities to isolated patients in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The information technology improvements will include purchasing work stations, equipment, firewalls, monitors, network switches, IT wi-fi access, and conference room access. The Pinal Hispanic Council offers behavioral health servicesin the Coolidge, Eloy, and Douglas, Arizona communities.

borrower_name: SUN LIFE FAMILY HEALTH CENTER INC
funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for the construction costs, and machinery, equipment, and furnishings of a new 131,500 square foot healthcare facility to be built in Casa Grande, Arizona. The new facility will bring various locations together in one central location, and enable Sun Life Health Center to provide multiple services in one location, improve patient care and experience, and allow patient retention and increase the volume of new patients in the area. The area has been federally designated as a low-income medically underserved population; and a mental health professional and dental health professional shortage area. The facility will offer primary care, womens OBGYN clinic, pediatric medicine, imaging, x-ray, MRI, and ultrasound, behavioral health, laboratory, and pharmacy services, nutrition classes, patient outreach program, administrative functions, call center, and patient care coordination.

funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment investment will be used to purchase and install renewable energy equipment. BACA FLOAT #3 LLC will purchase and install ground-mounted solar photovolatic (PV) that will provide 100 percent of the power to the well pumps, irrigation system and ranch office. The solar is spread across eight different sites to power wells and remote irrigation. The project will produce 731,818 kilowatt hours (kWh) of renewable electricity per year, which is the equivalent 112 gasoline-powered passenger vehicles driven for one year. The project will save $5,488 in the first full year.

naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment investment will be used to purchase and install renewable energy equipment. Nogales-Texas Properties LLC will purchase and install a 779,000 kilowatt (kW) roof-mounted solar photovoltaic (PV) system. The system will generate 1,423,418 kilowatt hours (kWh) of renewable electricity per year, which is the equivalent of 1,528,449 miles driven by an average gasoline-powered passenger vehicle. This project is estimated to save $95,383 annually. The solar array will be on a warehouse for cool food storage in Rio Rico, Arizona.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used expand the capacity of the Regional Economic Development Center at Yavapai College. The mission of this organization is to enhance the quality of life in Yavapai County by providing regional support through job creation, business and workforce development, technological innovation, and regional collaboration. The project is anticipated to assist six small businesses in Yavapai County, create 26 jobs, and save 23 jobs.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND. RENEW ENERFY SYSTEMS GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Page Springs Cellars Inc. purchase and install a battery backup system designed to augment the previously installed solar generation systems. Page Springs Cellars is a winery and vineyard. The new battery system is rated as a 54 kW battery that could save the business a full days revenue in a power outage, saving $8,000 a day per incident. This business has averaged about five outages a year. The battery system will offer backup power to allow the business to continue operating in case of an outage.

Echo Canyon Vineyards is a winery located in Cornville, Arizona. This project will eliminate the need for the business to purchase electricity from the local utility company, resulting in a savings of $724 dollars per month that can be invested back into agritourism activities.

funding_code: DISCRETION RURAL MICROPENTERPR DEV ORG
naics_industry_sector: Finance and Insurance (52)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to support Verde Valley Regional Economic Organization (VVREO) efforts to provide technical assistance to rural entrepreneurs. VVREO provides access to resources for regional business creation and expansion with the goal of rural prosperity. This project will support a revolving loan fund available to microentrepreneurs located in the Verde Valley region of Yavapai County, Arizona.

funding_code: SECD COMMUNITY FACILITY GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Desert Star Community School, a nonprofit public charter school in rural Cornville, Arizona. The project is the second phase funded by Rural Development and will improve major components of the building complex to better serve students and staff. The original layout does not allow for adequate public access nor does it comply with Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) requirements. In addition, the administration building location prevents adequate supervision over campus public access. This project will assist to remove and replace the mobile structure currently used as an administration building and construct a larger building, demolish a deteriorating and inadequate earthship 1978 structure and replace it with functional classrooms, an ADA-compliant restroom facility, and main public campus entrance. The improvements will increase the functional space and improve the organization of classrooms, administrative offices, campus flow and security.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by the Black Canyon Community Health Cetner to purchase equipment, make fiberoptic upgrades for telecommunications equipment, and add a telehealth case management position. This will enable the health center to expand the telehealth services and testing and vaccination services during the COVID-19 pandemic. This health center serves rural patients in underserved communities.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and equip a van to be used as a mobile telemedicine unit for the health care organization Northland Cares. This mobile unit will educate, provide health care and prevention services, and provide COVID-19 testing and vaccinations to persons with autoimmune deficiencies, in the remote areas of Yavapai and Mohave Counties. Northland Cares provides a range of outpatient services for people living with HIV/AIDS, and prevention services for those at risk of sexually transmitted infections. Their clients are at high risk of being estranged, isolated and stigmatized by community members, family and society. The COVID pandemic exposed those with already compromised immune systems to the devastating effects of the COVID-19 virus, and Northland Cares has been inundated with requests for health care services from individuals who cannot travel to one of their facilities.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESIDENTIAL INTELLECTUAL AND DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITY FACILITIES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to support the nonprofit Steps to Recovery as they meet the needs of healthcare clients. Steps to Recovery, located in Cottonwood, Arizona, will complete the buildout of a facility and purchase necessary equipment and supplies. These purchases will include information technology, COVID testing, and personal protection equipment, office furnishings, as well as pay for employee training, program development, and COVID telehealth access.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Arts, Entertainment, and Recreation (71)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase the equipment and parts to repair the heating ventilation and air conditioning (HVAC) system of the Verde Valley Archaeology Center. The Center is a nonprofit corporation, which preserves archaeological sites and collections to encourage a deeper understanding of prehistory and American Indian history in the Verde Valley of Arizona. The organization has multiple HVAC units in its museum which maintain the proper temperatures to preserve artifacts. This system is failing and without investing in its repair, the artifacts are at risk of damage.

funding_code: (SECD) CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
naics_description: LESSORS OF OTHER REAL ESTATE PROPERTY
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete renovations for a new recovery center in Cottonwood, Arizona. Steps to Recovery Homes is a nonprofit serving healthcare clients in a substance abuse recovery setting. The completed center will improve its ability to expand client services including social enterprises and job training programs.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a conveyor belt system for the Haven Community Food Pantry. The Haven Community Methodist Church donates the basement of their church for the communitys food pantry operations. This food pantry receives weekly food pantry donations of fresh, frozen, and non-perishable food, clothing, household and hygiene products one level lower than the street level. This conveyor belt system will eliminate the need for the food pantry volunteers to have to carry heavy boxes of donations down the 12 narrow and deep cement stairs from the street level to the basement door, improving operations overall.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist a non-profit charter school, Running River School Inc., to purchase a building as a permanent location for its classrooms and administration. Running River School supports grades one through eight in Sedona, Arizona. The school will no longer be limited by a competitive commercial lease market, which hampered its ability to expand enrollment and will provide better financial flexibility for the school to grow its programing and capacity.
