funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make infrastructure improvements to the town of Jeromes wastewater treatment plant. The towns treatment plant is aging and is not compliant with the states Department of Environmental Quality standards for exceeding contaminant levels. The plant is operating below design capacity and in order to bring the plant within safety standards a supporting system will be constructed. This project also includes additional collection lines, manholes, and improvements to access roads.

funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make infrastructure improvements to the town of Jeromes wastewater treatment plant. The towns treatment plant is aging and is not compliant with the states Department of Environmental Quality standards for exceeding contaminant levels. The plant is operating below design capacity and in order to bring the plant within safety standards a supporting system will be constructed. This project also includes additional collection lines, manholes, and improvements to access roads.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install renewable energy equipment. San Luis Warehouse & Transfer Company will purchase and install a 120 kilowatt DC roof-mounted solar PV system. The system will generate 204,545 kilowatt hours of renewable electricity per year, which is the equivalent 31.2 gasoline-powered passenger vehicles driven for one year. This project is estimated to save $32,727 annually with prices near $.16 per kWh. The solar array will be on a warehouse used for food storage in San Luis.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to rehabilitate and equip a building in Gadsden, Arizona with the necessary furniture and equipment to provide services to the area. Campesinos Sin Fronteras is a nonprofit organization providing improved access to health care, behavioral health, social services, workforce development, and similar resources for agricultural workers. This project will enable Campesinos Sin Fronteras to expand their COVID education, testing, vaccines, and other relief to this low-income farmworker community.

borrower_name: REGIONAL CENTER FOR BORDER HEALTH, INC.
funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two modular mobile units, equipment, supplies, and staffing to provide COVID-19 testing and vaccines (Pfizer, Moderna, and Johnson & Johnson), and provide medical primary care services to the medically underserved and distressed communities of Parker in La Paz County, Dateland in Yuma County, and other outlying residents who are otherwise unable to access medical services.

borrower_name: REGIONAL CENTER FOR BORDER HEALTH, INC.
funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Regional Center for Border Healths need to purchase 5 modular mobile units, equipment, supplies, furnishings, and staffing to provide complete COVID supportive services to indigent clients in the region of the Colorado River Indian Tribe.

borrower_name: REGIONAL CENTER FOR BORDER HEALTH, INC.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: OFFICES OF PHYSICIANS, MENTAL HEALTH SPECIALISTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for the Regional Center for Border Health to purchase equipment, staffing, training, and establish a comprehensive integrated rural health primary and behavioral telehealth clinic and services for individuals being treated for COVID-19 who need to be quarantined or in isolation in Yuma and La Paz Counties.

borrower_name: REGIONAL CENTER FOR BORDER HEALTH, INC.
funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide additional financial assistance for Regional Center for Border Health, Inc. to complete the expansion of the 22,742 square foot medical complex in Somerton, Arizona. This facility will increase the organizations capacity for behavioral health services, the College of Health Careers, infrastructure, technology, and administrative operations. This expansion will enable Regional Center for Border Health, Inc. to add services and offer more vocational technical programs for the surrounding communities of Somerton, San Luis, Gadsden, and Yuma.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system improvements in Tacna, Arizona. The county of Yuma will construct a new water treatment and distribution system, remove and replace more than 1,000 linear feet of aging or low capacity pipe to include service connections, and construct a new water storage tank and groundwater well at a new location away from the residential area. The current system is more than 40 years old and is deemed unfeasible to rehabilitate. The Arizona Department of Environmental Quality placed an Administrative Order on the water system, deeming the water non-drinkable due to high Arsenic levels dating back to 2011.

program: SEARCH - Special Evaluation Assistance for Rural Communities and Households Grant (WEP)
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to prepare a Preliminary Engineering Report and Environmental Report as a study of the sewer system for two subdivisions in Yuma County, Arizona. The rural communities are in need of sewer service and properly preparing for it will minimize project costs and environmental impact.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
naics_description: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IN BIOTECHNOLOGY (EXCEPT NANOBIOTECHNOLOGY)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help complete a study for local forestry, transportation, and sawmill businesses to supply needed materials and services that support biofuel, renewable chemical, and biogas manufacturing plants in southern Apache County, Arizona. The project will carry out planning, analyses, and technical assistance for a Bioeconomy Development Opportunity (BDO) Zone certification. It also will provide assistance to local economic-development bodies to leverage the BDO Zone rating. This will help bring business customers to the area to buy local bioeconomy products and services and help create jobs.

funding_code: SECD BUSINESS OPPORTUNITY GRANT - SECD
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop architectural plans and a cost estimate to build a 25,000-square-foot Regional Energy and Education Technical (REET) Center in the city of St. Johns Light Industrial Park at St. Johns Industrial Airport in Arizona. Powered by green energy, the facility will be an advanced business and technology center also providing vocational and workforce training to Apache and Navajo counties. There are planned closings of several nearby coal plants that provide high-paying jobs in this two-county area. The project goal is to expand other industries and job opportunities in the region.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY RBCS BUSINESS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop, implement, and manage a rural learning program. The project will provide education and job training, workshops, and assistance for employment and job advancements. It also will provide employment opportunity resources to the Din reservation community.

funding_code: SMALL SOCIALLY DISADVANTAGED PRODUCER GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Dine Community Development Corporation to conduct a feasibility study and develop a business plan for a potential reservation-based housing cooperative. The goal of the project is remove barriers and provide other housing options to Navajo families.

funding_code: NATIVE AMERICAN TRIBES COMMUNITY FACILITY GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
naics_description: ALL OTHER MISCELLANEOUS SCHOOLS AND INSTRUCTION
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase the materials needed to complete a livestock holding facility, steel indoor structure, utility support to the building and grounds, and foundation work for Dine Colleges new agriculture education facility. Once completed, the Dine College will use the space to provide education classes and training on handling livestock.

naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the non-profit Southeastern Arizona Government Organization with administering the Energy Resiliency Network (ERN). ERN will focus on small energy efficiency improvement and renewable energy system projects as well as assisting distressed and disadvantaged agricultural producers and rural small businesses to apply for Rural Energy for America Program funds. ERN helps with energy assessments and project identification, finance, design, permitting, and SAM enrollment as well as education and training.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct an addition to Copper Queen Community Hospital in Bisbee, Arizona. The 27,000 square foot addition will house operating rooms, pre- and post-operative areas, sterile processing area, and a new inpatient beds unit. Once completed, services will relocate from the current facility, and department areas will be repurposed for outpatient behavioral health care with tele-psych, specialty physician offices, expanded pharmacy, and an educational and training center for staff. The Bisbee Hospital Association is partnering with other members of the Southern Area Hospital Association in support of this project. The project will support the improved health outcomes of the southern Arizona community, facilitate access to local high caliber health care, and create sustainable economic development through quality job creation.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to remodel a vacant county-owned building in Bisbee, Arizona, into a modern animal shelter facility. In partnership with the Humane Society of Southern Arizona and Friends of the Bisbee Animal Shelter, the shelter will have 10 dog kennels and a separate room for cats. It will serve all Cochise County, including Bisbee, Sierra Vista, Douglas, Benson, and Hereford, Arizona.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
project_name: FY23 Q1 REAP 120 KW DC PV
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Retail Trade (44-45)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 120 kilowatt (kW) DC solar photovoltaic (PV) system to displace annual electric use for Junction Enterprises Inc. The PV system will be roof mounted, fix tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $27,521 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 187,723 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power 26 homes for one year. The system was designed to displace 89 percent of the annual electric demand.

funding_code: TEST
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the Energy Community Partnership (RECP) provide members of the Navajo Nation that do not currently have access to electricity an electrical connection at their homes. The RECP will implement a project scope beginning with the identification of 100 home sites, within the former Bennett Freeze area. The RECP partners will then install 100 small, contained, off-grid and secured solar PV arrays with lithium-ion battery/solar charger/inverter systems. The homeowners will receive a 10-year service contract with Navajo Power Home LLC for the operation and maintenance of this community scale distributed renewable energy system. The homeowners will also receive instruction on the system and be taught how to become their own power system manager. After ten years each of the 100 homes will have the option to contract for an additional 10 years or ownership will be transferred to the homeowner.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 17.8 kilowatt (kW) DC roof top solar photovoltaic system with a 110 kilowatt (kWh) high volt battery for a business in Colorado City, Arizona. The system is expected to save this business $2,043 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 31,096 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power four homes annual energy use. funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create, develop, and carry out a five-year economic development plan for Joseph City, Arizona. The project will help provide technical assistance in finance, marketing, and business development to local businesses.

funding_code: RBCS OPPORTUNITY NATIVE AMERICAN GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: ADMINISTRATION OF HUMAN RESOURCE PROGRAMS (EXCEPT EDUCATION, PUBLIC HEALTH, AND VETERANS' AFFAIRS PROGRAMS)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Hopi Relief develop the Hopi Resource Center. The investment will help plan for and secure a business site to include the creation of the facility design and engaging in contract procurement. The project will develop a multi-purpose food warehouse and resource center for the community on Hopi land.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY RBCS BUSINESS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create a multifaceted learning center, community kitchen, and food hub to promote and foster small and emerging food businesses focused on traditional Hopi foods. Hopi Tutskwa Permaculture Institute is an Indigenous-led community nonprofit on the Indigenous Hopi Reservation in Northern Arizona. The project will develop a business plan for the learning center, provide technical assistance to small and emerging businesses, and renovate and equip a building.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY RBCS BUSINESS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: ADMINISTRATION OF URBAN PLANNING AND COMMUNITY AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop community-based plans for the Dilkon Chapter of the Navajo Nation, Arizona. The project will establish plans for broadband, an internet service provider,and economic and community development leadership training. It will help supply small-business development and financing resources plus strategic instruction to access opportunities and overcome economic and industrial development barriers.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY RBCS BUSINESS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide technical assistance to regenerative-economyfarming and ranching entrepreneurs in the southwestern corner of the Navajo Nation, Arizona. The project involves 10 workshops and 150 hours of technical assistance to enhance regenerative agricultural skills, focusing on farm-to-school and farm-to-table goods and services. This training will help increase production quantity and quality and build business skills, including business planning, recordkeeping, branding, and marketing. The project also will expand distance-learning resources to reach more regenerative-business entrepreneurs. A majority of the project is located in a persistent-poverty county. The service area contains numerous distressed communities and opportunity zones.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network to provide high-speed internet. This network will benefit 4,126 people, 58 businesses, two farms and 14 educational facilities in Gila, Graham and Pinal counties in Arizona. San Carlos Apache Telecommunications Utility Inc. will make high-speed internet affordable by participating in the Federal Communications Commissions (FCC) Affordable Connectivity Program. This project will serve San Carlos Land Area Representation and socially vulnerable communities in Gila, Graham and Pinal counties.

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND COST OVERRUN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide additional financing to construct a hybrid Fiber-to-the-Premises and Fiber-to-the-Node fixed wireless system throughout the Peach Springs, Arizona Hualapai Nation service area. The service areas include 1,492 households, six educational facilities, one health care center, and three critical community facilities spread over 54 square miles.

funding_code: TELECOMMUNICATION VARIABLE RATE

In addition to the loan funds, general funds of $6,278,033 will be contributed to accomplish the project. Table Top Telephone Companys 5,021 subscribers will benefit from this investment.

funding_code: FERTILIZER PRODUCTION EXPANSION PROGRAM
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help offset the costs associated with purchasing additional equipment to increase production. Growers Market, Inc. has been in business since 1985 and is located in Arizona. Using green waste from commercial producers they can create an eco-friendly fertilizer that helps to divert 190,000 tons of organic waste over a 4-year period. By grinding waste at the source, it will also reduce greenhouse emissions by 4,300 metric tons. They expect to expand current compost production from 64,000 yards per year to 464,000 yards per year within five years.

project_name: Water Distribution, Storage Tank & Pump Station
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) 306C  WATER ONLY (COLONIAS)
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct new facilities for the Maricopa Mountain Domestic Water Improvement District to meet applicable health and sanitary standards. The out of district arsenic removal and treatment will be moved to the existing fill site and office; two additional wells and storage will be added; disinfection and arsenic and nitrate treatment will be added as needed; and a distribution system connecting a nearby existing subdivision will be installed adding 237 home sites to the overall system.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to acquire a three-story, 65-guestroom Best Western Inn and Suites in Nogales, Santa Cruz County, Arizona. The project will improve the economy in this distressed community and persistent poverty county. It will save 12 jobs and create 12 jobs.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a fix-tilt, grid-tied solar panel system on the roof of a 156,000 square foot refrigerated storage facility in Santa Cruz County, Arizona. This system will displace 1,373.4 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year, saving this rural small business $89,686 annually. This is the energy equivalent of powering 189 typical American homes for one year.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
borrower_name: BMV COLD STORAGE LLC - DBA SUN DEVIL
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Transportation and Warehousing (48-49)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a solar photovoltaic system on the roof of a 33,503 square foot cold food warehouse in Santa Cruz County Arizona. The 344.9 kilowatt (kW) DC solar photovoltaic system will be fix tilt, and grid tied. It will save $48,077 and replace 638,271 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is estimated to offset 100 percent of the annual energy costs for the building. This is enough energy to power 53 typical American homes for one year.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
naics_description: FRESH FRUIT AND VEGETABLE MERCHANT WHOLESALERS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Divine Flavor LLC, a grape importer, install a solar photovoltaic system on the roof of a refrigerated warehouse, displacing 74 percent of the annual electric usage. This project is expected to save $55,872 per year. It will replace 830,083 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to electrify 114 homes for one year.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a photovoltaic solar system to help a rural hotel replace 99 percent of the current annual energy consumption. This project includes 382 rooftop panels and two parking canopies with an additional 372 solar panels. This project will displace $53,450 in utility costs and 763,577 kilowatt hours (kWh) of purchased power a year. This is the equivalent of 1,390,851 miles driven by an average gasoline car or equivalent to 106 typical homes annual electric use.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Acacia Land & Storage LLC, the owner of a cold food storage building in Santa Cruz County Arizona, install a 779.9 kilowatt (kW) DC rooftop solar photovoltaic (PV) system. The PV system will be roof mounted, fixed tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $94,975 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 1,363.5 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power 187 homes.

The facility will increase the availability of the emergency room, urgent care, and hospital services in this rural community. The micro-hospital and urgent care facility will be leased to an operator that will staff and operate the facility. Forty jobs are expected to be created.

naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase the Best Western Prescottonian in Prescott, Arizona. The subject property is a 121-room limited service hotel. The project will create two jobs and save 26 jobs and will continue to assist in meeting the lodging demand created by tourism. meetings, and conventions in this rural community.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide job training and placement through the continued expanded workforce development programt to individuals recently recovered from alcohol- or substance-abuse addiction. The organization has partnered with recovery-friendly businesses in the area to provide stable and reliable employees. Steps to Recovery Homes in Cottonwood, Arizona will serve Yavapai CountysVerde Valley area.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
project_name: FY23 Q1 REAP SOLAR 870.5 KW DC
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 870.48 kilowatt (kW) DC solar photovoltaic (PV) system to displace the electric use at this short-term RV park in Cottonwood, Arizona. The PV system will be three elevated arrays, fixed-tilt and grid tied, and used for shaded parking. This system is expected to save this business $42,632 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 1,421,098 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power 196 homes annual energy use. The system was designed to displace 80 percent of the annual electric demand.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install 31.065 kilowatt (kW) DC to offset the electricity used by a motel. The photovoltaic system will be roof mounted, fixed tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $7,917 annually. The solar system will produce and use 56,350 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power seven gasoline powers cars for one year. The system is designed to displace 50 percent of the annual electric demand.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
borrower_name: B.M. WAGNER L.P. DBA SUNSET VILLAGE
project_name: FY23 Q1 REAP SOLAR PV 32 KW PV
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 32 kilowatt (kW) DC solar photovoltaic (PV) system to displace the electricity used at the offices and central common building for the Sunset Village senior living facility. The PV system will be roof mounted, fixed-tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $7,899 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 49,919 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power five homes annual energy use. The system was designed to displace 70 percent of the annual electric demand of this office and common use building.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 23.4 kilowatt (kW) on two roofs at a hotel property in Sedona, Arizona. The solar PV will produce and use 43,645 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power six homes. The system was designed to displace 100 percent of the annual electric demand.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to improve the water system in western Sedona, Arizona. This project will replace and extend public system water and service lines, including valves and hydrants; rehabilitate four water-storage tanks; install an arsenic treatment system; and replace meters. Arsenic levels in the water supply have exceeded allowable levels of the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality. Most of the system has been in existence since 1953 and parts of it have become inoperable.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
project_name: FY24 Q2 IRA REAP 614.9 KW PV
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
naics_description: FRESH FRUIT AND VEGETABLE MERCHANT WHOLESALERS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development REAP investment will be used to install a 614.9 kilowatt (kW) solar photovoltaic (PV) on the roof of a building owned by Chucho Produce LLC in Nogales, Arizona. The PV system will be roof mounted, fix tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $108,465 annually. The solar PV will produce and use 1,090,558 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power 97 homes. The system was designed to displace 100 percent of the annual electric demand for this refrigerated food warehouse.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
project_name: FY24 Q2 IRA REAP 145.6 KW DC
funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a 145.6 kilowatt (kW) direct current (DC) solar photovoltaic (PV) system on the roof of Circle Z Ranchs open-air arena in Patagonia, Arizona. The PV system will be roof mounted, fix tilt and grid tied, and is expected to save this business $25,769 annually. The system will produce and use 255,299 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which is enough energy to power 35 homes. The system was designed to displace 148 percent of the annual electric demand.
